{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/cms-gatsbyjs","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"88e81ab2-edc8-5544-8ce6-c4144cf07b36","html":"<h2 id=\"introduction\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#introduction\" aria-label=\"introduction permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Introduction</h2>\n<p>As I have previously mentioned, <a href=\"/admin-ui-gatsby-static-site-generator\">NetlifyCMS is one of the most flexible “CMS” applications</a> on the market at the moment. In the past you had to tweak both GatsbyJS and Netlify service configurations, so that the output of first was useful for the second. I shared about these details in a <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/blog/2017-11-06-migrate-hugo-gatsby/#admin-panel\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">story about migrating from Hugo to GatsbyJS</a>. Few weeks after these shared stories, Netlify released <a href=\"https://www.netlify.com/blog/2017/12/07/open-source-netlify-cms-hits-1.0-bringing-git-based-content-management-to-static-sites-everywhere/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">NetlifyCMS 1.0</a>. I think this release is a big milestone for the project because it involved a lot of work on <a href=\"https://github.com/netlify/netlify-cms/issues?q=is%3Aissue+is%3Aopen+sort%3Acomments-desc+label%3A%22area%3A+design%22\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">design perspective</a> but also on authentication and integration parts which make the product easier to adopt.</p>\n<p>A bit more than a month after this release, I have the feeling not many know about the improvements available. I blame the holiday season of December :) And so in this blog post I’ll share my personal impressions. I believe NetlifyCMS is still one of the best tools to have together with a static site generator, and it’s also well-integrated with another great service - Netlify.</p>\n<h3 id=\"starting-a-project\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#starting-a-project\" aria-label=\"starting a project permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Starting a project</h3>\n<p>When I published my thoughts on using NetlifyCMS and GatsbyJS together to make a modern web site with an admin panel, I started to get questions on twitter how I made a given project and how I organised a repository. My reply was always pointing to <a href=\"https://github.com/kalinchernev/kalinchernev.github.io\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">the repository storing the github pages for my username</a>. A friendly way to say RTFM - the blog posts were the documentation I thought - just fork the repo and tweak it!</p>\n<p>Some people succeeded taking an example, others didn’t. The ones who didn’t, didn’t because making websites can be the job of a site builders and not developers. Being a site builder with experience and good expectation management with the client is good. So, starting a project should be easy. A successful WCMS product sometimes means starting with a visually appealing base, and being able to involve developers, where and when necessary on a later stage. WordPress with wordpress.com is an example of that. Start small, build a prototype, demo it, get trust for more work on a project, succeed, that’s what I mean :)</p>\n<p>And there’s the first good news - starting with GatsbyJS and adding an administration panel hasn’t been easier!</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go and <a href=\"https://www.netlifycms.org/docs/start-with-a-template/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">select the right starter</a>:</li>\n</ol>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 960px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/eb16966fb80a713b698da64c620b034a/78ed4/netlifycms-gatsbyjs-starter.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 49.583333333333336%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/eb16966fb80a713b698da64c620b034a/8ac56/netlifycms-gatsbyjs-starter.webp 240w,\n/static/eb16966fb80a713b698da64c620b034a/d3be9/netlifycms-gatsbyjs-starter.webp 480w,\n/static/eb16966fb80a713b698da64c620b034a/e46b2/netlifycms-gatsbyjs-starter.webp 960w,\n/static/eb16966fb80a713b698da64c620b034a/f992d/netlifycms-gatsbyjs-starter.webp 1440w,\n/static/eb16966fb80a713b698da64c620b034a/882b9/netlifycms-gatsbyjs-starter.webp 1920w,\n/static/eb16966fb80a713b698da64c620b034a/a4016/netlifycms-gatsbyjs-starter.webp 2566w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/eb16966fb80a713b698da64c620b034a/8ff5a/netlifycms-gatsbyjs-starter.png 240w,\n/static/eb16966fb80a713b698da64c620b034a/e85cb/netlifycms-gatsbyjs-starter.png 480w,\n/static/eb16966fb80a713b698da64c620b034a/d9199/netlifycms-gatsbyjs-starter.png 960w,\n/static/eb16966fb80a713b698da64c620b034a/07a9c/netlifycms-gatsbyjs-starter.png 1440w,\n/static/eb16966fb80a713b698da64c620b034a/29114/netlifycms-gatsbyjs-starter.png 1920w,\n/static/eb16966fb80a713b698da64c620b034a/78ed4/netlifycms-gatsbyjs-starter.png 2566w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/eb16966fb80a713b698da64c620b034a/d9199/netlifycms-gatsbyjs-starter.png\"\n            alt=\"Select the GatsbyJS starter\"\n            title=\"Select the GatsbyJS starter\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li>Give your project a name</li>\n</ol>\n<p><img src=\"/f5d9f6cb0aba54886c68678d9a3d81db/gatsbyjs-starter-progress.gif\" alt=\"Naming your project\"></p>\n<ol start=\"3\">\n<li>Accept invitation</li>\n</ol>\n<p>When you start the creation of a new project, the new identity service of Netlify will create your user 1, and will send you an invite for it, just accept it :)</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 960px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/bd87e499fde82ad4298b6f4dc77b5d7b/61583/accept-netlify-invite.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 35.833333333333336%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/bd87e499fde82ad4298b6f4dc77b5d7b/8ac56/accept-netlify-invite.webp 240w,\n/static/bd87e499fde82ad4298b6f4dc77b5d7b/d3be9/accept-netlify-invite.webp 480w,\n/static/bd87e499fde82ad4298b6f4dc77b5d7b/e46b2/accept-netlify-invite.webp 960w,\n/static/bd87e499fde82ad4298b6f4dc77b5d7b/f992d/accept-netlify-invite.webp 1440w,\n/static/bd87e499fde82ad4298b6f4dc77b5d7b/1548f/accept-netlify-invite.webp 1616w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/bd87e499fde82ad4298b6f4dc77b5d7b/8ff5a/accept-netlify-invite.png 240w,\n/static/bd87e499fde82ad4298b6f4dc77b5d7b/e85cb/accept-netlify-invite.png 480w,\n/static/bd87e499fde82ad4298b6f4dc77b5d7b/d9199/accept-netlify-invite.png 960w,\n/static/bd87e499fde82ad4298b6f4dc77b5d7b/07a9c/accept-netlify-invite.png 1440w,\n/static/bd87e499fde82ad4298b6f4dc77b5d7b/61583/accept-netlify-invite.png 1616w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/bd87e499fde82ad4298b6f4dc77b5d7b/d9199/accept-netlify-invite.png\"\n            alt=\"Accept Netlify invite\"\n            title=\"Accept Netlify invite\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<ol start=\"4\">\n<li>Set credentials</li>\n</ol>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 960px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ad28900e6e18dedf56f042283daac745/a2b91/netlifycms-set-credentials.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 57.91666666666667%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/ad28900e6e18dedf56f042283daac745/8ac56/netlifycms-set-credentials.webp 240w,\n/static/ad28900e6e18dedf56f042283daac745/d3be9/netlifycms-set-credentials.webp 480w,\n/static/ad28900e6e18dedf56f042283daac745/e46b2/netlifycms-set-credentials.webp 960w,\n/static/ad28900e6e18dedf56f042283daac745/f992d/netlifycms-set-credentials.webp 1440w,\n/static/ad28900e6e18dedf56f042283daac745/882b9/netlifycms-set-credentials.webp 1920w,\n/static/ad28900e6e18dedf56f042283daac745/1ab77/netlifycms-set-credentials.webp 3360w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/ad28900e6e18dedf56f042283daac745/8ff5a/netlifycms-set-credentials.png 240w,\n/static/ad28900e6e18dedf56f042283daac745/e85cb/netlifycms-set-credentials.png 480w,\n/static/ad28900e6e18dedf56f042283daac745/d9199/netlifycms-set-credentials.png 960w,\n/static/ad28900e6e18dedf56f042283daac745/07a9c/netlifycms-set-credentials.png 1440w,\n/static/ad28900e6e18dedf56f042283daac745/29114/netlifycms-set-credentials.png 1920w,\n/static/ad28900e6e18dedf56f042283daac745/a2b91/netlifycms-set-credentials.png 3360w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/ad28900e6e18dedf56f042283daac745/d9199/netlifycms-set-credentials.png\"\n            alt=\"NetlifyCMS accepting the invite and setting personal credentials\"\n            title=\"NetlifyCMS accepting the invite and setting personal credentials\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>If you want to invite others to contribute to your new website, or you want to change your email, you can use Netlify Identity console to manage users.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 960px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/efd21bc58c13ff4e743a26d09c895f08/0f529/netlify-identity-management.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 60.83333333333334%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/efd21bc58c13ff4e743a26d09c895f08/8ac56/netlify-identity-management.webp 240w,\n/static/efd21bc58c13ff4e743a26d09c895f08/d3be9/netlify-identity-management.webp 480w,\n/static/efd21bc58c13ff4e743a26d09c895f08/e46b2/netlify-identity-management.webp 960w,\n/static/efd21bc58c13ff4e743a26d09c895f08/464f9/netlify-identity-management.webp 1259w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/efd21bc58c13ff4e743a26d09c895f08/8ff5a/netlify-identity-management.png 240w,\n/static/efd21bc58c13ff4e743a26d09c895f08/e85cb/netlify-identity-management.png 480w,\n/static/efd21bc58c13ff4e743a26d09c895f08/d9199/netlify-identity-management.png 960w,\n/static/efd21bc58c13ff4e743a26d09c895f08/0f529/netlify-identity-management.png 1259w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/efd21bc58c13ff4e743a26d09c895f08/d9199/netlify-identity-management.png\"\n            alt=\"Netlify identity management console\"\n            title=\"Netlify identity management console\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<ol start=\"5\">\n<li>Enjoy your CMS :)</li>\n</ol>\n<p>You will be automatically redirected the administration pages of your new site! Enjoy! :)</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 960px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/1cca45673ad8ab2d04c10184429cbc4f/6f464/netlifycms-admin-pages.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 35.416666666666664%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/1cca45673ad8ab2d04c10184429cbc4f/8ac56/netlifycms-admin-pages.webp 240w,\n/static/1cca45673ad8ab2d04c10184429cbc4f/d3be9/netlifycms-admin-pages.webp 480w,\n/static/1cca45673ad8ab2d04c10184429cbc4f/e46b2/netlifycms-admin-pages.webp 960w,\n/static/1cca45673ad8ab2d04c10184429cbc4f/f992d/netlifycms-admin-pages.webp 1440w,\n/static/1cca45673ad8ab2d04c10184429cbc4f/0699c/netlifycms-admin-pages.webp 1464w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/1cca45673ad8ab2d04c10184429cbc4f/8ff5a/netlifycms-admin-pages.png 240w,\n/static/1cca45673ad8ab2d04c10184429cbc4f/e85cb/netlifycms-admin-pages.png 480w,\n/static/1cca45673ad8ab2d04c10184429cbc4f/d9199/netlifycms-admin-pages.png 960w,\n/static/1cca45673ad8ab2d04c10184429cbc4f/07a9c/netlifycms-admin-pages.png 1440w,\n/static/1cca45673ad8ab2d04c10184429cbc4f/6f464/netlifycms-admin-pages.png 1464w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/1cca45673ad8ab2d04c10184429cbc4f/d9199/netlifycms-admin-pages.png\"\n            alt=\"NetlifyCMS administration pages\"\n            title=\"NetlifyCMS administration pages\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3 id=\"the-administration-panel\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#the-administration-panel\" aria-label=\"the administration panel permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>The administration panel</h3>\n<p>One would expect that going to the <a href=\"https://www.netlifycms.org/docs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">official docs</a>, there would be a short overview or a tutorial about the features of the product. However, this is not the case, most probably because it’s so simple :)</p>\n<h4 id=\"content-management\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#content-management\" aria-label=\"content management permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Content management</h4>\n<p><img src=\"/403d59530315f51be9197c2db7d2d819/netlifycms-create-blog-post.gif\" alt=\"Create a post\"></p>\n<p>Clicking on “Publish” will put the content in the main branch of the repository and will trigger the build.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 960px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/5c903d449b44ffc552f84a4f9c15aa87/8698d/netlify-build-settings.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/5c903d449b44ffc552f84a4f9c15aa87/8ac56/netlify-build-settings.webp 240w,\n/static/5c903d449b44ffc552f84a4f9c15aa87/d3be9/netlify-build-settings.webp 480w,\n/static/5c903d449b44ffc552f84a4f9c15aa87/e46b2/netlify-build-settings.webp 960w,\n/static/5c903d449b44ffc552f84a4f9c15aa87/62b6b/netlify-build-settings.webp 1239w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/5c903d449b44ffc552f84a4f9c15aa87/8ff5a/netlify-build-settings.png 240w,\n/static/5c903d449b44ffc552f84a4f9c15aa87/e85cb/netlify-build-settings.png 480w,\n/static/5c903d449b44ffc552f84a4f9c15aa87/d9199/netlify-build-settings.png 960w,\n/static/5c903d449b44ffc552f84a4f9c15aa87/8698d/netlify-build-settings.png 1239w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/5c903d449b44ffc552f84a4f9c15aa87/d9199/netlify-build-settings.png\"\n            alt=\"Netlify build settings\"\n            title=\"Netlify build settings\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>If you rather have an additional moderation step before content lands into production, you use the <a href=\"https://www.netlifycms.org/docs/configuration-options/#publish-mode\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"><code class=\"language-text\">publish_mode</code></a>. For this, you’ll need to change the code of the repository (the starter) created under your Github username.</p>\n<h4 id=\"other-settings\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#other-settings\" aria-label=\"other settings permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Other settings</h4>\n<p>Content management features being quite straight-forward, by default the starter provides defaults which are common sense. For more advanced features and configurations options in the administration pages, you’ll need to <a href=\"https://www.netlifycms.org/docs/configuration-options/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">use the <code class=\"language-text\">config.yml</code></a> file in the repository as described in the docs.</p>\n<p>In terms of GatsbyJS, this file should always be placed in the <code class=\"language-text\">static/admin</code> folder in order to be accessible by <code class=\"language-text\">window.netlifyIdentity</code>. Documentation pages already describe <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/docs/caching/#static-files\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">how static files are handled</a>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"github\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#github\" aria-label=\"github permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Github</h3>\n<p>Although there’s the NetlifyCMS for providing eye-candy and easy UI for content management, one can still use the “regular” content management workflows developers have - using the repository on Github to add new content and change existing content :)</p>\n<h4 id=\"deploying-changes\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#deploying-changes\" aria-label=\"deploying changes permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Deploying changes</h4>\n<p>Pushing changes to main branch (master by default) will trigger the Netlify service to run another build of the project:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 960px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/df05cb0a19279ee703310995b8c418e9/d8817/netlify-listening-repository-changes.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 61.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/df05cb0a19279ee703310995b8c418e9/8ac56/netlify-listening-repository-changes.webp 240w,\n/static/df05cb0a19279ee703310995b8c418e9/d3be9/netlify-listening-repository-changes.webp 480w,\n/static/df05cb0a19279ee703310995b8c418e9/e46b2/netlify-listening-repository-changes.webp 960w,\n/static/df05cb0a19279ee703310995b8c418e9/e8403/netlify-listening-repository-changes.webp 1238w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/df05cb0a19279ee703310995b8c418e9/8ff5a/netlify-listening-repository-changes.png 240w,\n/static/df05cb0a19279ee703310995b8c418e9/e85cb/netlify-listening-repository-changes.png 480w,\n/static/df05cb0a19279ee703310995b8c418e9/d9199/netlify-listening-repository-changes.png 960w,\n/static/df05cb0a19279ee703310995b8c418e9/d8817/netlify-listening-repository-changes.png 1238w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/df05cb0a19279ee703310995b8c418e9/d9199/netlify-listening-repository-changes.png\"\n            alt=\"Netlify build settings\"\n            title=\"Netlify build settings\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>This workflow is similar to Heroku or other PaaS solutions.</p>\n<h4 id=\"previewing-changes\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#previewing-changes\" aria-label=\"previewing changes permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Previewing changes</h4>\n<p>When moderation workflows are enabled, creating a draft from NetlifyCMS administration pages means that the tool will create a new pull request to the main branch on your behalf. You can do the same just as you are used to do working with the repository directly - creating a new branch locally and pushing it to a branch for a pull request.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.netlify.com/blog/2016/07/20/introducing-deploy-previews-in-netlify/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Netlify previews</a> are a popular useful feature <a href=\"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/936c33a262eba0d3e053e67396079c34507f5cb8/docs/docs/deploy-gatsby.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">used by GatsbyJS project</a> and many others.</p>\n<h3 id=\"conclusions\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#conclusions\" aria-label=\"conclusions permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Conclusions</h3>\n<p>I hope this short tutorial would be useful to those searching for an Admin UI for a static site generator, and most specifically GatsbyJS. The process has been greatly simplified which hopefully will further increase the adoption of the JAM stack.</p>\n<p>The Gatsby Starter is welcoming, easy to get a GatsbyJS site up and running, so why not use this opportunity?</p>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/cms-gatsbyjs","tagSlugs":["/tag/jam-stack/","/tag/java-script/","/tag/gatsby-js/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2018-01-19T00:00:00+00:00","description":"Thoughts on integrating Gatsby.js with Netlify CMS.","tags":["JAMStack","JavaScript","GatsbyJS"],"title":"Having a CMS for GatsbyJS - easier than ever!","socialImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/cms-gatsbyjs"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","3691206191","401334301"]}